   "source": [
    "# Eigenvalue Results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "import opstool as opst\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We use the built-in arch bridge example and visualize it:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=1024x768>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "opst.load_ops_examples(\"ArchBridge\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot\n",
    "opst.vis.pyvista.set_plot_props(notebook=True)\n",
    "fig = opst.vis.pyvista.plot_model()\n",
    "fig.show(jupyter_backend=\"static\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "### Eigen vectors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In structural dynamics, ``eigenvectors`` play a crucial role in understanding the behavior of structures under dynamic loads. They provide insights into how a structure deforms or vibrates at specific natural frequencies (eigenvalues). These vectors, often referred to as mode shapes, are fundamental in modal analysis and dynamic response studies."
   ]
  },
